<taxonomicName box="[475,620,1731,1754]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Pygommatius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pygommatius</taxonomicName>
montanus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Scarbrough
</taxonomicName>
, terminalia. Male, 30–32. Lateral, dorsal, and ventral views; 33. Gonostylus, lateral view; 34. Aedeagus lateral view. Female, 35–36. Dorsal and ventral views; 37. Spermatheca; 38. Genital fork.
</paragraph>
